cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.CL, cs.CR 

The paper deals with logic programming semantics and epistemic logic programs, which are topics closely related to artificial intelligence and logic. Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses unfounded sets and splitting, which are concepts from logic and set theory, making cs.LO a likely sub-category as well. Additionally, the paper mentions stable model semantics, which is a popular approach in logic programming, making cs.PL a possible sub-category. The paper also deals with formal properties of epistemic semantics, which could fall under cs.CL (computational logic) or cs.CR (cryptography and security).
